Designer Simulation Robotic
Designer Simulation Robotic
Location:  Singapore
Salary:  GBP0 - GBP1 per annum + benefits Designer Robotic Simulation – Permanent – Singapore, China – Negotiable Salary
A Leading supplier of automated production systems requires a Designer Robotic Simulation to focus on perfection the robotic design processes of the projects considering the companies quality and environmental manuals whilst doing this. You will also be required to partially take on tasks from project’s Project Designer and will report directly to the team leader.
Your responsibilities include as follows;
Providing cost effective drawings and modifying of (draft) designs, compositions, parts lists and also pre ordered lists
Running robot simulations
Checking of drawings and assembly activities carried out by third party employees and contractors and reporting any disruptions in the project process and inform the Project Designer or Project engineer about the project progress
Create OLP robot paths (OLP Programming)
To be considered for the role you will need a minimum experience of 3years in operations after successfully completing your senior secondary vocational education. Ideally the client is looking for a candidate who has studied Mechanical Engineering or has equivalent education background.
This opportunity is based in Singapore, China. The role as Designer Robotic Simulation offers a competitive salary which is negotiable and an attractive benefits package
We can only consider candidates who are eligible to live and work in China. The client is happy to consider candidates from outside the local area but no relocation support is provided.
